definition.value: A cinnamate ester rusulting from the formal condensation of cinnamic acid with any alkyl alcohol.
An aromatic amide obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group of phenylacetic acid with the exocyclic amino group of 4-(5-amino-6-benzylpyrazin-2-yl)phenol.
A polyprenol triphosphate where the polyprenol component is farnesol.
A CDP-glycerol having unspecified acyl groups (most commonly fatty acyl groups) at the 1- and 2-positions.
